The article discusses the recent wave of shootings in communities across America and reflects on the anniversary of a shooting in Highland Park, Illinois. It highlights the efforts of Illinois Governor J.B. Pritzker, Highland Park Mayor Nancy Rotering, and others to take action against gun violence, including the banning of assault weapons and high-capacity magazines. However, it acknowledges that more needs to be done to address the epidemic of gun violence, such as requiring safe storage of guns, ending gun manufacturers' immunity from liability, and implementing universal background checks. The article urges other states to follow Illinois' lead and calls on Republican lawmakers in Congress to support meaningful gun control reforms.